   <body>
      <section>The <uicontrol>Life Cycle Monitoring LCM – Actions</uicontrol> page lists all the possible actions to be performed by the FSR.</section>
      <section>
         <fig expanse="page">
            <image href="../Images/service_port_lcm_action_menu_0000145535.png"
                   scalefit="yes"
                   placement="inline"/>
         </fig>
      </section>
      <section>
         <title>Available Actions</title>
         <table pgwide="1">
            <tgroup cols="2">
               <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="15%"/>
               <colspec colname="col2"/>
               <thead>
                  <row>
                     <entry valign="top">Action
#</entry>
                     <entry valign="top">Description</entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody>
                  <row>
                     <entry>001–006</entry>
                     <entry>
                        <uicontrol>Acknowledge “...” Reminder</uicontrol>
                        <p>Definitively acknowledge a pending alert. This alert may already
have been temporarily acknowledged via the display. After performing
this action, the pop-up will not be repeated on the display.</p>
                        <p>
                           <note>This will not automatically restart the counter to show the
alert again in the future (see below).</note>
                        </p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>012–016</entry>
                     <entry>
                        <uicontrol>Restart “...” Reminder</uicontrol>
                        <p>Restart a counter with the actual date as the start date. The
alert will be shown again after the defined period. This action must
be performed by the FSR after the corresponding preventive maintenance
has been carried out.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>022–026</entry>
                     <entry>
                        <uicontrol>Set “...” duration before first reminder</uicontrol>
                        <p>Change the default values set for the individual counters.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>032–036</entry>
                     <entry>
                        <uicontrol>Set “...” Counter Start Date</uicontrol>
                        <p>Set a specific start date for a counter which is different from
the date automatically set under <uicontrol>Start Counters Now</uicontrol> and <uicontrol>Acknowledge “...” Reminders</uicontrol>.</p>
                        <p>This action can be used to set the correct start dates for
each of the counters after a HMI replacement.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>101</entry>
                     <entry>
                        <uicontrol>Enable / Disable LCM Reminders</uicontrol>
                        <p>Enable
or disable the display of LCM pop-up alerts. This setting only disables
the pop-up messages from appearing on the display. All LCM functions
are still running.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>102–103</entry>
                     <entry>
                        <uicontrol>Set time window start</uicontrol> / <uicontrol>Set
time window end</uicontrol>
                        <p>Configure the time window when the LCM
alerts are displayed. In case a counter elapses, the alert will occur
on the HMI the next time this window is reached.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>104</entry>
                     <entry>
                        <uicontrol>Set reminder repeat number</uicontrol>
                        <p>Configure
the number of repeats of a LCM pop-up after it has been temporarily
acknowledged. After the set repeat number, the pop-up will not be
displayed again.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>105</entry>
                     <entry>
                        <uicontrol>Set reminder repeat period</uicontrol>
                        <p>Configure
the time period between repeats of an LCM pop-up after it has been
temporarily acknowledged.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>106</entry>
                     <entry>
                        <uicontrol>Set web address</uicontrol>
                        <p>Configure the web
address displayed on the LCM alert pop-up.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </section>
